column5: Hey all.  Well it's about time I got a new PB!  I snuck off to the cottage this weekend to spend time with my family and snuck in some time fishing too.  Just before I got this fish I looked at my watch, looked at my father and said "see ya, it's walleye bite time".  Not even 30 min after I said that I hooked into this nice one; 25 1/4" long, 12" girth and 4 LB 12 OZ.  I missed 4 more as I was using a rather long stick worm so they were holding on to the worm and not hooked.  However it was a good bass fishing weekend with over a doz. landed (all camera shy as they were all in the 1LB range). Now all I need is the wind to work with me in 2 weeks and not be so bad so I can get the kids out in the boat too...  well, no more talk, here is the fish...
nice fish you got there  I have caught a bunch of walleye this year, but not one that was out of the slot size
Congrats, very nice fish indeed.  Joey
Awesome fish! Those are the ones I dream about! hahaha!
tks all, I wanted to let it go if I got any in the "eater" size but I didn't get any more in the boat...  but it did taste great and everyone did enjoy it...
A nice one for sure, Congrats on the new PB!!!
Beauty eye GBW Congrats on your PB Leechman
